In a large mixing bowl, combine carrots, potatoes, 1/2 cup SPLENDA(R), raisins, flour, baking soda, ground cinnamon, allspice, and ground cloves. Transfer mixture to a clean 1 pound coffee can. Secure wax paper over the top with a rubber band and place the filled can in a large pot with 2 to 3 inches of water. Cover the pot and bring the water to a simmer. Steam the cake for 2 hours. Serve warm. Buttery sauce: In a medium pot, combine butter or margarine, cream, 2/3 cup SPLENDA(R), and vanilla. Heat until the mixture is liquid. Spoon mixture over the warm carrot pudding to serve.